# Database schema reference

Authoritative Supabase tables. Use exact column names in queries — do not invent aliases or rename columns.

## `categories`
- `id` uuid PK, `slug` (unique), `name`, `sort_order`
- `created_at`, `updated_at`
- Read-only catalog — no insert/update from API routes (migrations only)

## `venues`
- `id` uuid PK, `slug` (unique), `provider_id` → `auth.users` (nullable)
- `category_id` → `categories` (NOT NULL)
- `name`, `description`, `short_description`, `location`, `district`, `address`, `latitude`, `longitude`
- `capacity_min` (default 10), `capacity_max` (default 500)
- `rating`, `review_count`, `is_featured`, `is_new`
- `image_url`, `images` (text[]), `amenities` (text[]), `operating_hours` (jsonb)
- `price_per_person` integer NOT NULL
- `contact_phone`, `contact_email`, `website`
- `created_at`, `updated_at`

## `venue_time_slots`
Recurring weekly pricing per venue (day-of-week granularity — **not hourly**).
- `id` uuid, `venue_id` → `venues`
- `day_of_week` integer 0–6 (0 = Sunday)
- `regular_price` NOT NULL, `sale_price` nullable, `is_on_sale` boolean (default false)
- `created_at`
- Unique constraint: `(venue_id, day_of_week)`

## `venue_bookings`
- `id` uuid, `venue_id` → `venues`, `user_id` → `auth.users` (nullable)
- `booking_date` date (day-level — no start_time/end_time for day bookings)
- `guest_count` integer, `total_price` integer
- `status`: `pending` | `confirmed` | `cancelled` (default `confirmed`)
- `created_at`, `updated_at`

## Query patterns

```typescript
// Always join categories via embed syntax
supabase.from("venues").select("*, categories(slug, name)")

// Availability check for a date range
supabase
  .from("venue_bookings")
  .select("id, booking_date")
  .eq("venue_id", venueId)
  .gte("booking_date", start)
  .lte("booking_date", end)
  .eq("status", "confirmed")

// Upsert time slot (onConflict required)
supabase
  .from("venue_time_slots")
  .upsert({ venue_id, day_of_week, ...pricing }, { onConflict: "venue_id,day_of_week" })
```
